Program: Discovery
Title: Life in Antarctica
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxcm
Last Broadcast Date: 26 March 1999
Various speakers give descriptions of their experiences in Antarctica. Scientists and researchers tell their tales of life living on the South Pole. Many claim it was probably the most intense and interesting experience of their lives. The continent has the lowest ever recorded temperature and has ice 5km thick. Show less